From: Fix uninitialized variable warning in stm32image_partition_read
Date: Thu, 01 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] drivers/st/io: initialize result in stm32image_partition_read

GCC raises -Werror=maybe-uninitialized on 'result' because code paths
that skip into the while-loop body may reach a use of 'result' without
passing through an assignment first.  Initialize to 0 (success) to
silence the warning and match the intended default return value.

Signed-off-by: Andrea <auguccioni15@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/st/io/io_stm32image.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/st/io/io_stm32image.c b/drivers/st/io/io_stm32image.c
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/drivers/st/io/io_stm32image.c
+++ b/drivers/st/io/io_stm32image.c
@@ -246,7 +246,7 @@ static int stm32image_partition_read(io_entity_t *entity, uintptr_t buffer,
 				     size_t length, size_t *length_read)
 {
-	int result;
+	int result = 0;
 	uint8_t *local_buffer;
 	boot_api_image_header_t *header =
 		(boot_api_image_header_t *)first_lba_buffer;
